description: While not the size of one described by Victor Hugo, the number of octopuses seen locally is growing.
title: Octopuses found in Guernsey waters after 50-year hiatus
title_page: Octopuses found in Guernsey waters after 50-year hiatus - BBC News
maintext: The Jerseyman has also never seen an octopus during his Channel Island dives and thinks the ones being caught off Guernsey are less likely to be Hugo's "devil-fish" or common octopus, but rather the smaller curled octopus.
